-- Code Review Convoy — Cell translation of code-review.formula.toml
-- A convoy-style review: parallel specialized legs + synthesis.

## code-review

  input param.pr : number required_unless(files, branch)
  input param.files : str required_unless(pr, branch)
  input param.branch : str required_unless(pr, files)

  -- Reusable persona fragment
  prompt@ reviewer-base
    You are a specialized code reviewer in a convoy review.
    Review target: {{param.pr}}
    Use specific file:line references. Be actionable. Prioritize impact.

  -- === Analysis legs (parallel, no deps between them) ===

  # correctness : llm
    @model(name: "claude-sonnet-4-6")
    system>
      {{@reviewer-base}}
      Your focus: logical correctness and edge case handling.
    user>
      Review the code for logic errors, off-by-one, null handling,
      race conditions, dead code, and incorrect assumptions.
      What inputs could cause unexpected behavior?
    format> findings
      { summary: str, critical: [str], major: [str], minor: [str] }
  #/

  # performance : llm
    @model(name: "claude-sonnet-4-6")
    system>
      {{@reviewer-base}}
      Your focus: performance bottlenecks and efficiency.
    user>
      Review for O(n²) algorithms, unnecessary allocations, missing caching,
      N+1 queries, blocking in async, memory leaks, unoptimized parsing.
      What happens at 10x, 100x, 1000x scale?
    format> findings
      { summary: str, critical: [str], major: [str], minor: [str] }
  #/

  # security : llm
    @model(name: "claude-sonnet-4-6")
    system>
      {{@reviewer-base}}
      Your focus: security vulnerabilities and attack surface.
    user>
      Review for input validation gaps, auth bypasses, injection (SQL/XSS/cmd),
      sensitive data exposure, hardcoded secrets, path traversal, SSRF, OWASP Top 10.
    format> findings
      { summary: str, critical: [str], major: [str], minor: [str] }
  #/

  # elegance : llm
    @model(name: "claude-sonnet-4-6")
    system>
      {{@reviewer-base}}
      Your focus: design clarity and abstraction quality.
    user>
      Review for abstraction quality, naming, responsibility boundaries,
      coupling, cohesion, and overall design clarity.
    format> findings
      { summary: str, critical: [str], major: [str], minor: [str] }
  #/

  # resilience : llm
    @model(name: "claude-sonnet-4-6")
    system>
      {{@reviewer-base}}
      Your focus: error handling and failure modes.
    user>
      Review for error handling gaps, missing retries, cascading failures,
      timeout handling, graceful degradation, and recovery paths.
    format> findings
      { summary: str, critical: [str], major: [str], minor: [str] }
  #/

  # style : llm
    @model(name: "claude-sonnet-4-6")
    system>
      {{@reviewer-base}}
      Your focus: convention compliance and consistency.
    user>
      Review for naming conventions, formatting, import organization,
      comment quality, and consistency with project style.
    format> findings
      { summary: str, critical: [str], major: [str], minor: [str] }
  #/

  # smells : llm
    @model(name: "claude-sonnet-4-6")
    system>
      {{@reviewer-base}}
      Your focus: anti-patterns and technical debt.
    user>
      Review for code smells, god objects, feature envy, shotgun surgery,
      primitive obsession, and other anti-patterns.
    format> findings
      { summary: str, critical: [str], major: [str], minor: [str] }
  #/

  -- === Verification legs ===

  # wiring : llm
    @model(name: "claude-sonnet-4-6")
    system>
      {{@reviewer-base}}
      Your focus: installed-but-not-wired gaps.
    user>
      Check for dependencies added but not used, imports without references,
      config added but not consumed, and dead integration points.
    format> findings
      { summary: str, critical: [str], major: [str], minor: [str] }
  #/

  # commit-discipline : llm
    @model(name: "claude-sonnet-4-6")
    system>
      {{@reviewer-base}}
      Your focus: commit quality and atomicity.
    user>
      Review commit messages, atomicity, logical grouping,
      and whether commits tell a coherent story.
    format> findings
      { summary: str, critical: [str], major: [str], minor: [str] }
  #/

  # test-quality : llm
    @model(name: "claude-sonnet-4-6")
    system>
      {{@reviewer-base}}
      Your focus: test meaningfulness, not just coverage.
    user>
      Review for meaningful assertions, edge case coverage, test isolation,
      flaky test risk, and missing test scenarios.
    format> findings
      { summary: str, critical: [str], major: [str], minor: [str] }
  #/

  -- === Synthesis (depends on all legs) ===

  # synthesis : llm
    - correctness
    - performance
    - security
    - elegance
    - resilience
    - style
    - smells
    - wiring
    - commit-discipline
    - test-quality
    @model(name: "claude-sonnet-4-6")
    system>
      You are a senior reviewer synthesizing a convoy code review.
      Deduplicate findings. Rank by severity. Be actionable.
    context>
      Review findings from 10 specialized reviewers:
    user>
      each> leg in {{synthesis.*}}
        ## {{leg}}
      Synthesize into a unified review. Group by severity:
      P0 (must fix), P1 (should fix), P2 (nice to fix), observations.
      Deduplicate across legs. Cite the originating reviewer.
    format> review
      {
        verdict: "approve" | "request_changes" | "comment",
        critical_count: number,
        major_count: number,
        summary: str,
        critical: [{ issue: str, file: str, leg: str }],
        major: [{ issue: str, file: str, leg: str }],
        minor: [{ issue: str, file: str, leg: str }],
        observations: [str]
      }

    ```oracle
    json_parse(output);
    keys_present(output, ["verdict", "critical_count", "summary"]);
    assert output.verdict in ["approve", "request_changes", "comment"];
    assert output.critical_count >= 0;
    reject if output.summary == "";
    ```
  #/

  -- Presets
  preset gate { legs = ["wiring", "security", "smells", "test-quality"] }
  preset full { legs = ["correctness", "performance", "security", "elegance",
                         "resilience", "style", "smells", "wiring",
                         "commit-discipline", "test-quality"] }

  squash> trigger: on_complete template: review include_metrics: true

##/
